  "name": "Power Supply Smoothing Demo",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "Power Supply Smoothing Demo",
    "description": "Right after USB power, a 1000µF capacitor sits on the center column from V+ to ground — a bulk supply cap like on a real board. Tap the tact button on the east branch (470Ω + red LED). The cap holds the rail up during each pulse so the supply does not dip as sharply. Compare lesson 30, where the same cap value is in parallel with the LED only. Cap + toward power; LED east at 90°."
  },
